ls conventions after Feb 1 9 Presidents budget message cuts scheduled war expenditures 19 billion in 1945 fiscal year Air lines cut passenger fares 6 12 per cent effective March 1 OPA announces interim rise eryg to 5 a ton on five basic steel products Blackout ordered on out door advertising lighting 11 ODT orders discontinuance of seasonal trains to resorts ef fective March 1 15 Street lights ordered dimmed to save coal 19 First quarter meat for civil ians cut 15 per cent 22 Sen Murray presents full employment bill 23 New controls on price and production of textiles and clothing announced ODT sets 5 day pf tlal embargo on rail shipments of civilian freight in northeastern states 26 Full embargo on civilian freight set for three days on east ern seaboard 27 Federal court rules seizure by government of Montgomery Ward properties illegal February 1 Parital four day embargo on civilian freight in eight eastern states 6 New fighter plane with rear propeller announced by Curtiss Wright 8 WFA cuts civilian soap supply to 85 per cent of 19401941 average Automobile industry halts reconversion planning as war needs"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-08-12T17:38:27.195Z", "group": ["ndnp/ncu", "university-of-north-carolina-chapel-hill-library-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78002169/1945-12-31/ed-1/?sp=6", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lily_ver01:data:sn78002169:0027955887A:1945123101:0838/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=433&w=321", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ncu:batch_ncu_lily_ver01:data:sn78002169:0027955887A:1945123101:0838/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=867&w=642", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lily_ver01/data/sn78002169/0027955887A/1945123101/0838.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new hanover", "united states", "new hanover county", "wilm